You can try to take a look at [$facet][1] operator which allows you to run mutliple separate queries and get results as single document. Then you can run [$concatArrays][2], [$unwind][3] and [$replaceRoot][4] to combine and promote your query results.

    db.sessions.aggregate([
        {
            $facet: {
                q1: [
                    { $match:{n:&quot;snat&quot;} },
                    { $project : {
                    _id : 0,sourceIp : &quot;$si&quot;,sourcePort : &quot;$sp&quot;,sourceNatIp : &quot;$tsi&quot;,sourceNatPort : &quot;$tsp&quot;, destIp : &quot;$di&quot;,destPort : &quot;$dp&quot;, trandisp: &quot;$n&quot;
                    }}
                ],
                q2: [
                    { $match:{n:&quot;dnat&quot;}},
                    { $project : {
                    _id : 0,sourceIp : &quot;$si&quot;,sourcePort : &quot;$sp&quot;,destinationNatIp : &quot;$tdi&quot;,destinationNatPort : &quot;$tdp&quot;, destIp : &quot;$di&quot;,destPort : &quot;$dp&quot; ,trandisp: &quot;$n&quot;
                    }}
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            $project: {
                all: {
                    $concatArrays: [ &quot;$q1&quot;, &quot;$q2&quot; ]
                }
            }
        },
        {
            $unwind: &quot;$all&quot;
        },
        {
            $replaceRoot: {
                newRoot: &quot;$all&quot;
            }
        }
    ])

[Mongo Playground][5]


  [1]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/facet/
  [2]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/concatArrays/index.html
  [3]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/unwind/index.html
  [4]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/replaceRoot/index.html
  [5]: https://mongoplayground.net/p/pKiwms5Vs7U

